The paper involves using a GAN model (StarGAN) for emotion recognition and generation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The creation of a new dataset and manual annotation of valence arousal values also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the focus on emotion recognition and generation suggests a potential application in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
